---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Valepath — Technology Due Diligence for PE Transactions"
  description="Structured technology assessment for PE-backed transactions. Quantified risk scoring, cost-to-fix estimates, and value creation roadmaps in 10–15 days."
>
  <div class="page">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="header">
      <div class="header__brand">Valepath</div>
      <nav class="header__nav">
        <a href="#framework">Framework</a>
        <a href="#deliverables">Deliverables</a>
        <a href="#track-record">Track Record</a>
        <a href="#about">About</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="nav-cta">Get in Touch</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>Technology due diligence for PE transactions.</h1>
      <p class="hero__lead">
        Quantified risk scoring, phased cost-to-fix estimates, and IC-ready value creation roadmaps. Delivered in 10&ndash;15 working days.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__offer">
        Most technology DD tells an Investment Committee the architecture has technical debt. Ours tells them it&rsquo;s &pound;2.4M to remediate over 18 months with a 3.2x ROI.
      </div>
      <div class="hero__ctas">
        <a href="#contact" class="btn">Schedule a Conversation &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/sample-dd-report.pdf" class="btn btn--secondary" download>Download Sample Report &darr;</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Framework -->
    <section class="section section--alt" id="framework">
      <h2>Assessment Framework</h2>
      <p>Eight dimensions, each producing a standardised 1&ndash;5 score against peer benchmarks and a quantified financial estimate.</p>
      <table class="scorecard">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th></th>
            <th>Dimension</th>
            <th>What we assess</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">1</span></td>
            <td>Architecture & Infrastructure</td>
            <td>Cloud maturity, system topology, technical debt, scalability ceiling, SPOFs</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">2</span></td>
            <td>Team & Organisation</td>
            <td>Headcount, composition, key-person risk, outsourcing mix, hiring feasibility</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">3</span></td>
            <td>Security & Compliance</td>
            <td>OWASP exposure, SOC 2 readiness, GDPR/NIS2 posture, incident history</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">4</span></td>
            <td>Data & Analytics</td>
            <td>Quality, governance, integration health, privacy, master data</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">5</span></td>
            <td>AI & Proprietary Technology</td>
            <td>Model portfolio, IP governance, training-data provenance, EU AI Act exposure, moat durability</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">6</span></td>
            <td>Cost Structure</td>
            <td>Total spend analysis, cloud optimisation, licence audit, cost-to-fix estimate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">7</span></td>
            <td>Delivery Capability</td>
            <td>DORA metrics, CI/CD maturity, QA practices, AI engineering leverage, backlog health</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">8</span></td>
            <td>Strategic Alignment & Bolt-on Readiness</td>
            <td>Roadmap fit, multi-tenancy & integration readiness, competitive moat, exit attractiveness</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <!-- Deliverables -->
    <section class="section" id="deliverables">
      <h2>Deliverables</h2>
      <p>Every engagement produces six artefacts, designed for direct use in IC materials and for the deal team post-close.</p>

      <div class="deliverables-stack">
        <!-- Risk Scorecard -->
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>Risk Scorecard</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">Standardised &middot; Comparable across deals</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sample-scorecard">
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Architecture</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 80%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">4/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Team</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 60%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">3/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row sample-row--alert">
              <span class="sample-dim">Security</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill sample-fill--alert" style="width: 40%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">2/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Data</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 80%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">4/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">AI & Proprietary</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 60%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">3/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Cost</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 60%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">3/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Delivery</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 80%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">4/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row">
              <span class="sample-dim">Strategic & Bolt-on</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 60%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">3/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="sample-row sample-row--composite">
              <span class="sample-dim">Composite</span>
              <div class="sample-bar"><div class="sample-fill" style="width: 65%;"></div></div>
              <span class="sample-score">3.25/5</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Cost-to-Fix -->
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>Cost-to-Fix Estimate</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">Quantified in GBP &middot; Phased &middot; Confidence intervals</span>
          </div>
          <table class="sample-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Phase</th><th>Initiatives</th><th>Investment</th><th>Timeline</th><th>ROI</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>P1: Quick wins</td><td>5</td><td>&pound;320K</td><td>0&ndash;3 months</td><td>Protects &pound;3.1M ARR</td></tr>
              <tr><td>P2: Foundation</td><td>6</td><td>&pound;1.20M</td><td>3&ndash;12 months</td><td>Unlocks bolt-on thesis</td></tr>
              <tr><td>P3: Optimisation</td><td>3</td><td>&pound;580K</td><td>12&ndash;24 months</td><td>Platform-grade profile</td></tr>
              <tr class="sample-total"><td>Total</td><td>12</td><td>&pound;2.10M</td><td></td><td>~&pound;11M value protected / unlocked</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Full DD Report -->
        <div class="deliverable-card deliverable-card--download">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>Full Due Diligence Report</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">14 sections &middot; 8 dimensions &middot; IC-ready PDF</span>
          </div>
          <div class="deliverable-card__body">
            <p>The complete deliverable: executive summary, 100-day plan, eight dimension assessments with peer-benchmarked scoring, risk scorecard, phased cost-to-fix, and deal structuring implications.</p>
            <p>Review an illustrative sample prepared for a fictional London mid-market LegalTech target.</p>
            <a href="/sample-dd-report.pdf" class="btn" download>Download Sample Report (PDF) &darr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Executive Summary -->
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>Executive Summary</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">2 pages &middot; IC-ready &middot; Go/no-go recommendation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="sample-summary">
            <div class="summary-verdict summary-verdict--go">RECOMMENDATION: GO WITH CONDITIONS</div>
            <p class="summary-text">Technology is a net enabler of the platform thesis, with a credible AI moat (18&ndash;24 month lead). Three material issues: (1) no SOC 2 Type II &mdash; 14% of ARR at contractual risk, (2) AI model training-data provenance undocumented &mdash; potential IP contamination, (3) multi-tenancy hard-coded &mdash; blocks efficient bolt-on integration. Total cost-to-fix: &pound;2.10M over 24 months. Recommended price adjustment: &minus;&pound;3.0M with &pound;1.5M escrow milestone-released over 18 months.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- First 100 Days Plan -->
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>First 100 Days &mdash; Operational Plan</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">Week-by-week &middot; Owner-assigned &middot; KPI baselines</span>
          </div>
          <table class="sample-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Window</th><th>Workstream</th><th>Outcome</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Days 1&ndash;14</td><td>Security</td><td>SOC 2 readiness assessment; pentest scheduled</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Days 14&ndash;30</td><td>Cost</td><td>Cloud and licence audit &mdash; &pound;200K+ savings identified</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Days 30&ndash;60</td><td>Compliance</td><td>GDPR / DSR automation deployed; DACH retention secured</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Days 60&ndash;90</td><td>Architecture</td><td>Bolt-on integration refactor scoped and costed</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Days 90&ndash;100</td><td>Governance</td><td>Tech steering committee; KPI dashboard live</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Deal Structuring Implications -->
        <div class="deliverable-card">
          <div class="deliverable-card__header">
            <strong>Deal Structuring Implications</strong>
            <span class="deliverable-card__tag">SPA-ready reps &middot; Escrow milestones &middot; Price adjustment</span>
          </div>
          <table class="sample-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Lever</th><th>Recommendation</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Price adjustment</td><td>&minus;&pound;3.0M from ask &mdash; itemised against ARR-at-risk and certain remediation</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Escrow</td><td>&pound;1.5M / 18 months, milestone-released against SOC 2 and AI provenance audit</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Reps & warranties</td><td>Enhanced: IP / training-data provenance, cybersecurity, AI regulatory compliance</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Earnout</td><td>&pound;4.0M cap tied to ARR growth, DACH segment, AI tier adoption</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Management retention</td><td>Founder-CTO lockup + knowledge-transfer milestones; AI team pool</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="#contact" class="btn" style="margin-top: var(--sp-5);">Discuss Your Next Deal &rarr;</a>
    </section>

    <!-- Testimonials -->
    <section class="section section--alt" id="testimonials">
      <h2>What Clients Say</h2>
      <div class="testimonials">
        <blockquote class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;Pedro excels at executing highly technical projects, asking the right questions and inspiring the team with a deep sense of focus and purpose.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Itamar Leizorek, CEO, Noxgen Biotech</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;He has a remarkable ability to foresee industry trends and identify strategic opportunities that others may overlook.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Jeronimo Mohar, Founder & CEO, Aleph RI</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;An excellent track record of building and leading high-performance technical teams to develop and implement software and data solutions.&rdquo;</p>
          <cite>Daniel Servitje, Co-Founder & CEO</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Track Record -->
    <section class="section" id="track-record">
      <h2>Track Record</h2>
      <p>Built on 13 years of entering companies, assessing their technology, building the fix, and handing off to internal teams.</p>
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__value">80+</div>
          <div class="stat__label">Assessments</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__value">9</div>
          <div class="stat__label">Industries</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__value">4</div>
          <div class="stat__label">ERP implementations</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat__value">$5M&ndash;$300M+</div>
          <div class="stat__label">Portfolio revenue</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="highlights">
        <div class="highlight">
          <span class="highlight__metric">+18% NOI</span>
          <span class="highlight__desc">Technology-driven value creation at a 285-room resort &mdash; 14 initiatives assessed and delivered</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight">
          <span class="highlight__metric">0 hrs unplanned downtime</span>
          <span class="highlight__desc">Industrial PLC automation for water-treatment plant &mdash; critical infrastructure reliability</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight">
          <span class="highlight__metric">5M+ items indexed</span>
          <span class="highlight__desc">Production AI infrastructure &mdash; RAG pipelines, vector databases, LLM APIs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight">
          <span class="highlight__metric">&ndash;25% maintenance costs</span>
          <span class="highlight__desc">IoT predictive maintenance &mdash; 90% of potential failures identified before occurrence</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--sp-4);">
        Full portfolio: <a href="https://velkan.io/case-studies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">velkan.io/case-studies</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- About -->
    <section class="section section--alt" id="about">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <div class="about-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>The Practice</h3>
          <p>Valepath provides structured technology due diligence for PE-backed transactions. Every assessment follows a standardised 8-dimension framework &mdash; including a distinct AI &amp; proprietary technology assessment and bolt-on integration readiness &mdash; producing peer-benchmarked risk scores and financial estimates designed to be lifted directly into an IC memo. We work with mid-market PE firms on deals where technology is a material factor in the investment thesis.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Pedro Rivera Torres Moir</h3>
          <p>Founder &amp; Principal. B.S. Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering (CU Boulder), Advanced Project Management (Stanford). Previously: Founder &amp; CTO of Velkan (80+ technology transformations, 2012&ndash;2020), Co-Founder &amp; CEO of Waffle (AI platform, 5M+ items), Co-Founder of Abraxas (venture builder, $150M+ portfolio). EU, US, MX citizen. London-focused.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="section" id="contact">
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>If you need technology risk quantified before a deal closes, or a value creation roadmap for a portfolio company.</p>
      <div class="contact-row">
        <button type="button" class="btn copy-email" data-email="pedro@valepath.com" aria-label="Copy email address pedro@valepath.com">
          <span class="copy-email__default">Email Us &mdash; pedro@valepath.com</span>
          <span class="copy-email__done" aria-hidden="true">Copied &check;</span>
        </button>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/pedrortm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://pedrortm.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pedrortm.com</a>
      </div>
      <script is:inline>
        document.querySelectorAll('.copy-email').forEach((btn) => {
          btn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
            const email = btn.getAttribute('data-email');
            try {
              await navigator.clipboard.writeText(email);
            } catch (err) {
              // Fallback for older browsers
              const ta = document.createElement('textarea');
              ta.value = email;
              ta.setAttribute('readonly', '');
              ta.style.position = 'absolute';
              ta.style.left = '-9999px';
              document.body.appendChild(ta);
              ta.select();
              document.execCommand('copy');
              document.body.removeChild(ta);
            }
            btn.classList.add('is-copied');
            setTimeout(() => btn.classList.remove('is-copied'), 1800);
          });
        });
      </script>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer>
      <span>&copy; 2026 Valepath</span>
      <span>London</span>
    </footer>

  </div>
</Base>
